title: My Favorite MCU Character
body:
After watching all of the MCU movies, I’ve come to the conclusion that Steve Rogers is my favorite character in it, which is saying a lot. There are so many amazing characters, mainly our heroes are so complex and human. I love Thor (especially in the latest movies), Tony, Nat, Clint, Quill, Loki, Wanda… I could literally name all my favorites but they would be at least half of the entire MCU. 

And yes, I always say that Spiderman is my favorite superhero, but that’s the thing. Often times, they neglect Peter Parker for the sake of Spiderman and even if I adore Tom Holland and what they did with Spiderman, how he’s so vulnerable and still learning… I just prefer how Peter Parker is written in Spiderman 2 and PS4 Spiderman, there’s something special in those for me. Still, I think Peter Parker is my favorite Marvel character (not MCU), and even then, he’s tied with another one.

Steve Rogers. Steve Rogers, man, he’s so great. I made a post about him before (x) saying how he’s true to himself even after the serum, and it’s one of the things that I like most about him, but I’m so in love with that character! How strong his morals are, how he always just wants to make good wherever he goes, how kind and wise he is, how much he cares about his friends and about people he doesn’t even know, how strong and determined he is, that he never gives up and always fights for what is right and for what he believes in. He’s such an amazing character, and Chris Evans is the only Cap for me. I just love this character so much, he’s so well written and so likable and I’m super fond of him.

summary:
SPOILERS (not much tho) for Winter Soldier #4 (2018-).
Miraculously in #4 Bucky stays physically unharmed, hallelujah! 😍 Loved...
body:
SPOILERS (not much tho) for Winter Soldier #4 (2018-).

Miraculously in #4 Bucky stays physically unharmed, hallelujah! 😍 Loved the artwork, especially facial expressions (still don’t get why Sharon looks so old though). The nerve RJ’s dad has, calling a WW2 hero and Avenger James Barnes just “Buck”. Seriously?! Should’ve punched him much sooner just for this😎 Speaking of punching. The cliffhanger is very cliffhanger-y, didn’t expect it.

True winner in #4 is Alpine the cat, of course. Being lovingly petted by two superheroes simultaneously? What a purrrfect life!

summary: Well, I made a drawing for International Women’s Day. Aaaaaand I was dragged behind by my inability to like the product I was...
caption:
Well, I made a drawing for International Women’s Day. Aaaaaand I was dragged behind by my inability to like the product I was making, and not giving myself enough of a head start to do it. (Also work is stressful, but most of the blame falls squarely on my shoulders) 

But, I wanted to do a drawing of many of the characters that had been so influential for me, from my earliest days to last week. All the fun and colorful characters that have filled my life with so much joy, and could pick me up no matter how down my life was. 

So from the bottom of my heart, a happy Interdimensional Women’s Day to all (no matter how late it may be ^^”)
